<br>
o  Make it a fast-casting AE stun with a long recast timer<br>
o  Make it a AE knockback centered on the caster<br>
o  Make it a larger mana sieve<br>
o  Leave as-is, but make it lure-based<br>
o  Leave as-is, but make it return the sieved mana to the caster<br>
o  Make it a long-duration single-target stun, 7-15 seconds<br>
o  Make it an atone spell for paladins<br>
o  Make it an AE mana drain<br>
o  Make it a curse that increases target's fizzle rate<br>
o  Make it a curse that make's target's next spell automatically fail<br>
o  Make it an interrupt proc with ac/atk debuff<br>
o  Make it an AE stun + Sta drain + channeling debuff + caster Sta drain<br>
o  Make it a 2-sec stun proc<br>
o  Make it double the casting time of target's spells<br>
o  Make it a fast-casting lure stun capable of interrupting any mob, including those immune to stuns<br>
o  Make it a stun shield<br>
<br>
All of these are great suggestions, but some don't fit the current theme of the spell. I will separate the ideas that support the current theme from the ones that suggest a new theme in my email to Absor from the Paladin community. Hopefully something good will come of this and we'll get a useful spell we all enjoy. <p><b><a href="http://www.serenity-within.com/View_Member.php?Name=Aelodyn" target="_blank">Aelodyn Autumnflame</a><br>Knight of Tunare<br><a href="http://www.serenity-within.com/" target="_blank">Serenity Within</a><br>The Nameless</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulordcalvaron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Calvaron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/19/02 3:20:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14497.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Stun shield Idea</span><hr size=1> The total idea of a stun shield is absolutly bad arse.  I mean come on, the chain stunning is done for us.<br>
